"""
Format:
If no score is available for a dimension, set it to null.

Evaluation:
Stage 1 → ≥60% win rate in val
Stage 2 → ≥75% in val in-domain = good. 78–82% = solid. ≥85% = very strong (depending on domain).

Rules:
Only needed message and chosen/rejected, the scores are not mandatory.
The chosen/rejected must share some dimensions and differ in others.
Mix pairs that differ subtly in one dimension (e.g., empathy) and pairs that differ in several.
Include multi-turn pairs to teach trajectory criteria (entity tracking, adjacency). Message number of turns: 1-turns 15%, 3-turns 40%, 5-turns 30%, 7-turns 15%. Chosen/rejected must be same turns length.
If the rejected usually have better stage 1 scores than chosen, the model will learn wrongly.
Mismatch: 55–65% → reasonable alignment between different datasets, < 55% = low → noticeable mismatch. Spearman 0.3–0.5 = moderate; <0.2 = low → noticeable mismatch.
The dialogues should be different from stage 1.
To calculate which one is the chosen/rejected, must use a different criterion than stage 1, but related (e.g. heads: coherence, empathy) to avoid mismatch.
"""

{
  "stage_2_dialogue_id": "YYY-nnnnnn", // ID for stage 2
  // "stage_1_dialogue_id": "XXX-nnnnnn", // Reference to original stage 1 dialogue
  // source of the dialogue, add more if needed
  "meta": {
    "source": "common_sense|multicultural|social",
    "split": "train|dev|test"
  },
  // metadata about the annotation for trazability
  "annotations": {
    "annotator_id": null,
    "method": "human|llm_judge",
    "model_judge": null,
    "notes": null
  },
  // shared prefix: common turns to chosen and rejected
  // ideally ends in USER turn (so the model has to predict the next assistant turn)
  "messages": [
    { "role": "user", "content": "Hi there, I had a really bad day today." },
    { "role": "assistant", "content": "I'm sorry to hear that. Want to tell me what happened?" },
    { "role": "user", "content": "My boss yelled at me even though it wasn’t my fault." }
  ],
  // differing turns: chosen responses
  "chosen": [
    { "role": "assistant", "content": "That must have felt unfair. I’m here for you." },
    { "role": "user", "content": "Thanks, I appreciate it." },
    { "role": "assistant", "content": "Do you want to unpack what happened so we can plan next steps?" }
  ],
  // differing turns: rejected responses
  "rejected": [
    { "role": "assistant", "content": "People get yelled at all the time; it’s not a big deal." },
    { "role": "user", "content": "It was really upsetting to me." },
    { "role": "assistant", "content": "You’ll get over it." }
  ],
  // Optional: If you pre-calculate Stage 1 targets to speed up training
  "chosen_objectives": null, // or a dictionary with your heads if you precompute them
  "rejected_objectives": null, // idem
  // Optional for filtering
  "preference": "chosen_over_rejected",
  "chosen_score": null, // Overall score for chosen response (0.0-1.0)
  "rejected_score": null, // Overall score for rejected response (0.0-1.0)
},